<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (ECSC, EC, EURATOM) No 3162/94 of 19 December 1994 amending Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 260/68 laying down the conditions and procedure for applying the tax for the benefit of the European Communities </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EST&Uuml;, E&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 3162/94, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;, EURATOM, EST&Uuml;) nr 260/68, millega on kehtestatud Euroopa &uuml;hendustele makstavate maksude kohaldamise tingimused ja kord 19. detsember 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing a Single Council and a Single Commission of the European Communities, and in particular the first paragraph of Article 28 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;htse n&otilde;ukogu ja &uuml;htse komisjoni asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 28 esimest l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Protocol on the Privileges and Immunities of the European Communities, and in particular Article 13 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste privileegide ja immuniteetide protokolli, eriti selle artiklit 13, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is a appropriate to extend the application of the tax for the benefit of the European Communities, on the terms and in accordance with the procedure laid down in Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 260/68 (3), to the salaries, wages and emoluments of the members of the organs of the European Investment Fund in the performance of their duties as such and the staff of the Fund, </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Euroopa &uuml;hendustele makstavate maksude kohaldamist m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 260/68 (3) etten&auml;htud tingimustel ja korras on otstarbekas laiendada Euroopa Investeerimisfondi organite liikmete ja k&otilde;nealuse fondi personali palkade, t&ouml;&ouml;tasude ja muude rahaliste tasude suhtes, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following Article is hereby inserted in Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 260/68: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lisatakse m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 260/68 j&auml;rgmine artikkel: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 12b </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 12b </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall apply to the members of the organs of the European Investment Fund in the performance of their duties as such, to members of its staff and to recipients of the pensions paid by the Fund who are included in the categories determined by the Council pursuant to the first paragraph of Article 16 of the Protocol on Privileges and Immunities, with regard to salaries, wages and emoluments and to disability, retirement and survivor's pensions paid by the Fund. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse Euroopa Investeerimisfondi organite liikmete ja personali suhtes ning nende pensionisaajate suhtes, kellele fond maksab pensioni, kui need isikud kuuluvad kategooriatesse, mis n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks privileegide ja immuniteetide protokolli artikli 16 esimese l&otilde;ike kohaselt, kui k&otilde;ne all on fondi makstavad palgad, t&ouml;&ouml;tasud ja muud rahalised tasud, invaliidsuspensionid, vanaduspensionid ja toitjakaotuspensionid." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 19 December 1994. </inglise>
